@startuml A3_02_component_enrollment_database_detailed
title Enrollment Database – Detailed View

skinparam rectangle {
  BorderColor #000000
  BorderThickness 1
}

package "Enrollment Domain Database (Postgres)" as ENROLLMENT_DB {
  
  rectangle "**Academic Structure**" as ACADEMIC {
    rectangle "• Departments\n• Majors, minors, concentrations\n• Courses\n• Prerequisites, co-requisites\n• Course sections (times, locations)" as ACADEMIC_TABLES
  }
  
  rectangle "**Requirements**" as REQUIREMENTS {
    rectangle "• Major requirements\n• Minor requirements\n• Concentration requirements\n• Course-to-requirement mappings" as REQUIREMENT_TABLES
  }
  
  rectangle "**Enrollment & Scheduling**" as ENROLLMENT {
    rectangle "• Student enrollments\n• Grades & transcripts\n• Enrollment deadlines\n• Schedule conflicts\n• Section capacity" as ENROLLMENT_TABLES
  }
  
  rectangle "**Financial Data**" as FINANCIAL {
    rectangle "• Tuition rates (by units, student type)\n• Fees (registration, course, etc.)\n• Course costs (books, materials)\n• Housing costs\n• Commuting costs" as FINANCIAL_TABLES
  }
  
  rectangle "**Transfer Data**" as TRANSFER {
    rectangle "• Transfer institutions\n• Transfer courses\n• Course equivalencies\n• Transfer policies" as TRANSFER_TABLES
  }
  
  rectangle "**People**" as PEOPLE {
    rectangle "• Students (major, minor, GPA)\n• Instructors\n• Accessibility features" as PEOPLE_TABLES
  }
}

' Enrollment Service queries
cloud "Enrollment Service\n(Layer 2)" as ENROLLMENT_SERVICE

ENROLLMENT_SERVICE --> ACADEMIC : course search, section lookup
ENROLLMENT_SERVICE --> REQUIREMENTS : degree audit, requirements matching
ENROLLMENT_SERVICE --> ENROLLMENT : enrollment status, deadlines, conflicts
ENROLLMENT_SERVICE --> FINANCIAL : budget calculation, cost estimation
ENROLLMENT_SERVICE --> TRANSFER : transfer equivalency lookup
ENROLLMENT_SERVICE --> PEOPLE : student data, instructor info

note right of ENROLLMENT_SERVICE
**Enrollment Assistance Use Cases:**
- Degree audit by major/minor/concentration
- Course search with filters (time, location, professor)
- Scenario comparison (full-time vs part-time)
- Schedule optimization with constraints
- Transfer course equivalency lookup
- Budget calculation (tuition, fees, costs)
- Enrollment deadline checking
- Prerequisite validation
end note

note bottom of ENROLLMENT_DB
**Data Sources:**
- SJSU Student Information System (SIS)
- SJSU Financial Systems
- SJSU Transfer Center
- Academic Departments
- Accessibility Resource Center

**Data Integration:**
- ETL pipelines from SIS (daily during registration)
- Financial data sync (weekly)
- Transfer data updates (weekly)
- Real-time capacity updates during registration
- Historical course data retention
end note

@enduml


